import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X'] = pd.to_datetime(data['X'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.scatterplot(x='X', y='Y', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X'] = pd.to_datetime(data['X'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='X', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['X'].median(), color='red', label=f'Median: {data["X"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Y'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Y'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Y', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Y'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['Y'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X'] = pd.to_numeric(data['X'], errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x='X', data=data)
    plt.axvline(x=data['X'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['X'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average value of X?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
